biogHists.text: Aaron Wills was a Quaker from Burlington County, New Jersey. He was born to Daniel Wills and Elizabeth Woolston on 23 June 1734 (old style). In 1758 he married Rachel Warrington, daughter of Henry Warrington and Elizabeth Bishop. Wills died on 29 April 1805.

relations.note: Aaron Wills was noted on a list of elders and ministers of Burlington Monthly Meeting.

relations.note: Aaron Wills married Rachel Warrington, sister of Hannah Warrington Buzby.
Aaron Wills married Rachel Warrington, sister of Joseph Buzby's wife Hannah.
Aaron Wills married Rachel Warrington, sister of Esther Hunt.
Aaron Wills married Rachel Warrington, sister of John Hunt's wife Esther.
Aaron Wills was a first cousin of Joshua Lippincott. Wills's father Daniel was the brother of Lippincott's mother Elizabeth Wills.
Aaron Wills sold land in Moorestown, New Jersey, to Adonijah Peacock in 1773.
Aaron Wills's son Samuel married Grace Rogers, the daughter of William Rogers and his second wife.
Aaron Wills married Rachel Warrington, sister of WIlliam Rogers's first wife Sarah.
Aaron Wills married Rachel Warrington, daughter of Elizabeth Bishop Warrington.
Aaron Wills married Rachel Warrington, daughter of Henry Warrington.
Aaron Wills married Rachel Warrington, sister of Joseph Warrington.
Aaron Wills married Rachel Warrington, sister of Rebecca Walton Warrington's husband Joseph.

resource.title: John Hunt papers, 1770-1828.
resource.abstract: John Hunt kept a diary for more than 40 years, recording Quaker concerns and daily events. This collections consists primarily of the manuscript journal, 1770-1800; fragments of 1805, 1806 & 1808; and 1814-1824. Of particular interest are the visits of prominent Quakers, including Elias Hicks and Jonathan Evans. There is also an account book, some correspondence received, and other miscellaneous materials. Correspondents include Ann R. Matlack, Asa Matlack, Elizabeth A. Lippincott, John Cox, Joseph Foulke, and Josiah Roberts.
